RE: [junit] What&#39;s delta?Finally, of course, there&#39;s the simplistic answer
that floating point operations aren&#39;t precise. You can&#39;t always be 100%
certain that f1 + f2 = f3, due to rounding errors (especially if any of the
values are themselves derived). The delta allows you to state the degree of
error.

To verify this statement, just try

System.out.println((1 / 0.9999) * 0.9999);

ciao, Ilja


